# see: http://vim.wikia.com/wiki/Copy,_cut_and_paste
M - move to top of screen
H - move to middle fo screen
L - move to bottom of screen

zt - scroll line with cursor to top of screen
zz - scroll line with cursor to center of screen 
zb - scroll line with cursor to bottom of screen 

f{char} - move to [count]'th occurrence of {char} to the right.

## CTRL-movements
CTRL-F/B - page down/up (forward/back)
CTRL-D/U - 1/2 page down/up 
CTRL O   - go to prev stored cursor location - will even go to previous files. 
CTRL I   - go to next stored cursor location
CTRL E/Y - scroll screen up/down

